fees.description: A $54.85 (GST Incl) fee may apply when your property is reconnected (including when you move). Fee may vary.
A $54.85 (GST Incl) fee may apply when your property is disconnected (including when you move). Fee may vary.
A fee of $15.00 (GST exempt) may apply if your bill is not paid by the due date.
A 0.27% fee (GST Incl) may apply to payments made by VISA debit card.
If you pay at an Australia Post outlet, a payment processing fee of the higher of $2.70 or 0.49% (incl GST) may apply.
$2.15 (incl GST) may apply for each paper bill.
A 0.65% fee (GST Incl) may apply to payments made by VISA credit card.
A 0.33% fee (GST Incl) may apply to payments made by Mastercard debit card.
A 0.64% fee (GST Incl) may apply to payments made by American Express credit card.
A 0.67% fee (GST Incl) may apply to payments made by Mastercard credit card.

electricityContract.terms: Offer not available in all areas or properties connecting for first time. Residential customers only. Visit originenergy.com.au/2889/Terms-and-conditions for more.
electricityContract.variation: We may vary the Charges (including their amount, nature and structure) by notice to you at any time. For increases, notice will be at least 10 business days prior, for decreases, the notice will be at least 5 business days prior to the effective date

incentives.description: If you take up Origin Go Zero Electricity, we will offset the greenhouse gas emissions from your electricity supply through Climate Active, a government-backed carbon neutral certification scheme. The cost is $2.00 per week(Incl. GST).

One credit per electricity account. If this Origin Go Variable electricity plan is still active with the customer on 30 September 2025, $50 (Incl. GST) credit will be applied to the customer's electricity account after that date. If the customer ends this Origin Go Variable electricity plan before that date, the customer will not receive any credit. Credit is not redeemable for cash.

eligibility.description: You are not eligible for this offer if you have Solar installed at the premise.
Not available for all areas or property types

Credit applied if you sign up by 29th September 2025, and the plan is still active on 30th September 2025, and you have not received a credit in the previous 12 months. Not redeemable for cash. Ergon only*.

greenPowerCharges.description: For 1.13 cents/kWh 25% of your electricity usage is matched with electricity from Government accredited GreenPower sources
For 2.25 cents/kWh 50% of your electricity usage is matched with electricity from Government accredited GreenPower sources
For 4.50 cents/kWh 100% of your electricity usage is matched with electricity from Government accredited GreenPower sources

solarFeedInTariff.description: You will receive 0 cents per kWh exported.

electricityContract.onExpiryDescription: At the end of the benefit period we may extend your current Energy Plan or set you up with a new Energy Plan but only if we have written to you first and you havent told us not to
electricityContract.additionalFeeInformation: You must pay us any charges your distributor imposes on us in relation to services performed by your distributor (or anyone else) at your supply address.
